com.acrolinx.javasdk.core.extraction

Class TypedCheckInformationImpl<DocumentType extends Document>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.acrolinx.javasdk.core.extraction.TypedCheckInformationImpl<DocumentType>
  • Type Parameters:
    DocumentType - The type of the Document used for extraction.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    CheckInformation, TypedCheckInformation<DocumentType>

    public class TypedCheckInformationImpl<DocumentType extends Document>
extends Object
implements TypedCheckInformation<DocumentType>
    The class CheckInformation is used to provide all document-related check information like the. Document part itself, the offset in the whole document and additional result information displayed in the result dialog.

      • TypedCheckInformationImpl

        protected TypedCheckInformationImpl(DocumentType document,
                         int offset,
                         boolean isCompleteCheck,
                         AdditionalData additionalData,
                         CheckScope checkScope,
                         boolean isUseServerSideXmlExtraction)
        Instantiates a new check information. A check information contains a Document containing your text and an offset where the text starts. The offset is added to all markings that you get by InlineCheckCallback#mark(Marking).
        Parameters:
        document - the document containing the text to check
        offset - the offset which is added to all Marking information. If you check the whole text the offset should be 0.
        additionalData - the additional result information
